ure signatures and synthesizes an appropriate adapter configuration on-the-fly. This eliminates the need for manual annotation, per-language engineering, or domain-specific updates. The significance extends beyond translation: AutoHyperFormer establishes a new paradigm for self-configuring AI systems that adapt intelligently to novel contexts using only intrinsic signal extraction. It enables deployment in rapidly evolving scenarios—such as crisis response or community-driven localization—where metadata is unavailable and speed is critical. Moreover, the emergent disentanglement offers interpretability: users can manipulate translation tone or syntax independently by editing the inferred codes. We also show how the learned prototypes can be visualized and reused across tasks (e.g., style transfer, dialect identification), amplifying downstream utility.",
